Deal-level data

Ally Auto Receivables Trust 2017-1

Summary

Ending number of receivables: 24,671

Remaining principal balance across all receivables: $164,978,593

Current Period Distribution

Cumulative Distribution

Forecast

Forecasted principal balances are based on a forecasted total amount distributed to interest and principal balances in future terms. These values are calculated using an ETS time series forecasting model. It uses the historic values as input to create the forecasted values (see bottom chart).

Remaining note principal balances are calculated in each period by subtracting the forecasted dsitribution amount from remaining note principal balances according to note seniority. In each period, the interest distribution amount is first calculated and subtracted from the forecasted distribution amount before applying the remaining distribution amount to the note principal balances for the next period.
